news_header: No crew members have been arrested in Sweden regarding the cable crime incident, according to Bulgarian Foreign Minister Georg Georgiev.
news_text: Bulgarian Foreign Minister Georg Georgiev stated that the crew members of the vessel involved in a cable crime in Sweden have not been apprehended. A preliminary investigation into suspected sabotage in the Baltic Sea has begun, as the vessel Vezhen, operated by a Bulgarian company, is suspected of damaging a communication cable between Gotland and Latvia. The company acknowledges the possibility of an accident but denies any sabotage.
